(COLLAR BUZZING)

01:46:26.315 --> 01:46:27.521
Gotcha.

01:46:28.288 --> 01:46:29.349
AMANDA: We have a visitor.

01:46:29.384 --> 01:46:30.590
(GRUNTS)

01:46:45.371 --> 01:46:48.007
JIGSAW: Cecilia Pederson,

01:46:48.042 --> 01:46:50.309
Parker Sears,

01:46:50.345 --> 01:46:53.243
you've each been
working a grift.

01:46:53.278 --> 01:46:55.113
Playing a role,

01:46:55.148 --> 01:46:56.976
working together

01:46:57.011 --> 01:47:00.347
continuing to play out
your scam.

01:47:00.383 --> 01:47:05.825
Never realizing that
you have been the marks
all night long.

01:47:05.861 --> 01:47:08.122
(HISSING)

01:47:12.731 --> 01:47:15.401
You were given a chance
for redemption,

01:47:15.436 --> 01:47:20.039
but at every turn,
you chose death,

01:47:20.074 --> 01:47:22.004
instead of life.

01:47:23.907 --> 01:47:26.809
JOHN: I promise you,
one way or another,

01:47:26.844 --> 01:47:29.142
it's all gonna work out
according to plan.

01:47:29.177 --> 01:47:31.946
JIGSAW: You have played
your last con game...

01:47:31.981 --> 01:47:34.348
-PARKER: No!
-...but not your last game.

01:47:34.383 --> 01:47:39.494
The two of you
have worked together
to destroy others.

01:47:40.061 --> 01:47:42.024
(PARKER GRUNTING)

01:47:43.960 --> 01:47:47.793
Now, you will work
against each other.

01:47:47.829 --> 01:47:49.603
-(GASPING)
-(THUDDING)

01:47:50.336 --> 01:47:53.167
Only one can survive.

01:47:54.107 --> 01:47:56.610
(GASPING)

01:47:57.409 --> 01:47:59.811
And the choice is yours.

01:48:00.709 --> 01:48:03.144
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:48:12.523 --> 01:48:13.688
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:48:13.723 --> 01:48:15.325
I thought you forgot about me.

01:48:15.360 --> 01:48:17.598
(CECILIA GRUNTING)

01:48:18.365 --> 01:48:19.996
You know I'd die for you, baby.

01:48:29.979 --> 01:48:31.678
(BOTH GRUNTING)

01:48:38.987 --> 01:48:39.983
CECILIA: Ah!

01:48:43.453 --> 01:48:45.659
(THUDDING)

01:48:54.969 --> 01:48:56.232
(GASPS)

01:48:56.268 --> 01:48:57.671
(GROANING)

01:48:57.707 --> 01:48:59.837
You know she's eventually
gonna kill you, too, right?

01:48:59.872 --> 01:49:02.472
-Fuck off, Amanda.
-JOHN: She's gonna burn you.

01:49:02.508 --> 01:49:04.238
You just can't see it yet.

01:49:14.517 --> 01:49:17.088
(GASPING)

01:49:17.124 --> 01:49:19.792
(GROANING)

01:49:31.599 --> 01:49:32.937
John!

01:49:37.308 --> 01:49:38.338
John!

01:50:05.006 --> 01:50:06.201
Gracias.

01:50:07.375 --> 01:50:08.841
Let's get you home, Carlos.

01:50:19.989 --> 01:50:23.650
(BEEPING)

01:50:23.686 --> 01:50:25.759
(ALARM BUZZES)

01:50:26.722 --> 01:50:29.422
(BREATH TREMBLING)

01:50:30.895 --> 01:50:33.096
(HOPEFUL INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

01:51:02.298 --> 01:51:04.292
(SLOW PIANO MUSIC PLAYING)

01:52:17.536 --> 01:52:20.137
(MUFFLED GRUNTING)

01:52:21.607 --> 01:52:24.245
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

01:52:24.280 --> 01:52:26.275
(TENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

01:52:36.753 --> 01:52:38.419
It's my war wound.

01:52:40.429 --> 01:52:42.192
JOHN: Where is your scar...

01:52:43.296 --> 01:52:44.429
Henry?

01:52:44.465 --> 01:52:45.695
(MUFFLED SCREAMING)

01:52:45.730 --> 01:52:47.098
Thank you, Detective,

01:52:48.132 --> 01:52:50.871
for locating
my fellow cancer patient.

01:52:58.147 --> 01:52:59.809
(SCREAMS)

01:52:59.844 --> 01:53:01.816
Out of all the men to cheat,

01:53:03.319 --> 01:53:05.281
you picked John Kramer?

01:53:06.254 --> 01:53:07.481
I mean...

01:53:09.119 --> 01:53:12.752
-I call that epic bad luck.
-(GASPS)

01:53:12.788 --> 01:53:14.092
Please...

01:53:14.824 --> 01:53:16.292
John, please.

01:53:17.663 --> 01:53:19.064
Please, don't kill me.

01:53:19.100 --> 01:53:22.067
That's the last thing that
you should be worried about.

01:53:23.501 --> 01:53:24.872
Now...

01:53:26.001 --> 01:53:28.242
I want to play a game.

01:53:28.277 --> 01:53:30.075
(DEVICE WHIRRING)

01:53:31.542 --> 01:53:33.478
No! No!

01:53:33.513 --> 01:53:35.608
(HENRY SCREAMING)

01:53:36.217 --> 01:53:37.879
No! No!

01:53:37.914 --> 01:53:41.185
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

01:53:45.958 --> 01:53:48.159
(THRILLING INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC
PLAYING)

